## Environment Setup
- Python 3.11 works best with our dependencies (FastAPI 0.95.2, Pydantic 1.10.7)
- When importing from src directory, either remove 'src.' prefix or ensure __init__.py exists
- Package names in check_dependencies.py should use pkg_resources instead of importlib for better detection

## WordPress & WooCommerce Integration
- WordPress Application Password must be exactly 24 characters long (including spaces)
- Application Password format: XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX (6 groups of 4 characters)
- For media uploads, use WordPress API endpoint (/wp-json/wp/v2/media) instead of WooCommerce endpoint
- Always verify user permissions before attempting media uploads
- Use Basic Auth with WordPress username and Application Password for media operations
- Implement proper error handling for 401 (Unauthorized) responses
- Add detailed logging for debugging authentication issues
- When uploading images, optimize them first (resize, compress) before sending to WordPress
- Clean up temporary image files after successful upload

